com.google.gwt.dev.util.editdistance
Class MyersBitParallelEditDistance

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.dev.util.editdistance.MyersBitParallelEditDistance
All Implemented Interfaces:
GeneralEditDistance, java.lang.Cloneable
public abstract class MyersBitParallelEditDistance
extends java.lang.Object
implements GeneralEditDistance, java.lang.Cloneable

Computes Levenshtein string-edit distance using the algorithm of Eugene Myers (see "A fast bit-vector algorithm for approximate string matching based on dynamic progamming", Journal of the ACM, 46(3): 395-415, 1999), using the reformulations of Heikki Hyyro (see "Explaining and Extending the Bit-parallel Approximate String Matching Algorithm of Myers") along with Gonzalo Navarro ("Faster Bit-Parallel Approximate String Matching", Proc. 13th Combinatorial Pattern Matching (CPM'2002)).

duplicate

public GeneralEditDistance duplicate()
Description copied from interface: GeneralEditDistance
Creates a duplicate (clone) of this distance engine, typically in order to use it in another thread (as the GeneralEditDistance contract does not specify thread safety). This method differs from Object.clone() in two ways: it is typed (to GeneralEditDistance); and, it must not throw an exception.

Specified by:
duplicate in interface GeneralEditDistance
Returns:
a clone of this instance.
